        <TextBlock x:Name="content" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="4,24,0,0" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16"><Run Text="The design step is when we are going to develop an algorithm for a small part of your program or problem. an Algorithm is a finite set of instructions that lead to a solution. In this lesson we will use pseudocode, which we will get more in depth with later in this lesson. Pseudocode is a written list of the individual steps needed to solve the problem, without using a programming language like c++. The pseudocode should be a list of all the necessary details to clearly outline the solution that we want."/><LineBreak/><Run/></TextBlock>
